{
  "texts": [
    "The study's focus revolves around the processing of input joint angles, which are used to determine the robot's posture and orientation by dictating the positions of its six links.",
    "Employing forward kinematics, as discussed in Section 2.4.2, we compute the homogeneous transformation matrix, which is employed in mapping the joint space coordinates (angles) to the Cartesian coordinates of the end-effector.During each cycle of operation, updates to the robot's joint angles are computed based on the input commands tailored to achieve specific tasks while adhering to environmental constraints.",
    "The forward kinematics calculations are then performed to find the new position and orientation of the robot's end-effector.",
    "Subsequently, a continuous collision detection algorithm evaluates the proposed movement trajectory for any potential collisions.",
    "If a collision threat is detected, the system has the capability to adjust the trajectory or halt the movement altogether, thereby safeguarding the robot and its surroundings from damage.This integration of forward kinematics with continuous collision detection mirrors real-world applications of robotics, particularly in contexts demanding realtime responsiveness."
  ]
}